RESEARCH
EXPERIENCE
Tuning of Thermal Conductivity of Monolayer Gallium Nitride Nano-ribbon:
An Equilibrium Molecular Dynamics Study
Equilibrium Molecular Dynamics simulations using Stillinger-Weber potential has been
deployed to compute the thermal conductivity of the nanometer-sized zigzag monolayer
GaN nano-ribbon(NR). Thermal transport dependence of monolayer GaN-NR on the
variation of length and width are explored. Furthermore, the impact of aluminium and
indium doping on the thermal conductivity of monolayer GaN-NR are also investigated.
